data.fullContent: It was originally called Enron Field. After Enron dropped its naming rights, the ballpark was temporarily renamed Astros Field. The park was renamed again when Minute Maid bought the naming rights. Because the ballpark is small and cozy, it is sometimes called "The Juice Box".
data.answer: 它最初被称为安然领域。安然公司放弃了冠名权后，棒球场暂时改名为阿斯特罗斯球场。美汁源购买了冠名权后，该公园再次更名。因为球场小而舒适，它有时被称为“果汁盒”。
